{"id": "859", "instruction": "Given $P(x) = 1 - x + x^2 - x^3 + x^4$ over the interval $0 \\leq x \\leq 1$, try to reduce the degree of $P(x)$ with an allowable error of 0.008. The result is ______.\n\nOptions:\nA. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 7} {1 4 0}-\\frac{4} {4} \\, x-\\frac{1} {5} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nB. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 8} {1 2 9}-\\frac{3} {4} \\, x-\\frac{1} {1} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{4} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nC. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 7} {1 2 8}-\\frac{3} {4} \\, x-\\frac{1} {4} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nD. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 7} {1 3 0}-\\frac{3} {3} \\, x-\\frac{1} {6} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nE. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 7} {1 2 8}-\\frac{0} {4} \\, x-\\frac{5} {4} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nF. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 9} {1 2 8}-\\frac{5} {4} \\, x-\\frac{0} {4} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{2} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nG. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 7} {1 1 7}-\\frac{3} {4} \\, x-\\frac{1} {4} \\, x^{1}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nH. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 3 5} {1 4 0}-\\frac{2} {4} \\, x-\\frac{2} {4} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nI. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 2 6} {1 2 9}-\\frac{3} {4} \\, x-\\frac{2} {4} \\, x^{3}+\\, x^{4} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$\nJ. $$\nP ( x )=\n\\frac{1 1 7} {1 2 8}-\\frac{3} {1} \\, x-\\frac{1} {3} \\, x^{2}+\\, x^{3} \\,, \\quad x \\in[ \\, 0 \\,, 1 \\, ]\n$$", "output": "C"}
